80" target="_self"><div class="h3 max-2-lines l-h-3">Building a Scientific Narrative</div></a></header><main><div class="displayAuthorAndTime"><span class="h6">Nathan Ni, PhD </span><span class="h6"> | Apr 15, 2024</span><span class="h6"> | 6 min read</span></div><div class="max-3-lines l-h-3">A strong narrative is as integral a part of science writing as it is for any other form of communication.</div></main><footer></footer></section></div><div class="ArticleSummary  CSDBorder" data-aos="fade-up"><section class="thumbnail">  <figure class="thumbnailWrapper"><a href="/the-fundamentals-of-academic-science-writing-71742" target="_self"><picture><source media="(min-width: 568px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-t.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 568px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-t.jpg" type="image/jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 400px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-s.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 400px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-s.jpg" type="image/jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 567px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-m.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 567px)" srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-m.jpg" type="image/jpeg"><img src="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71742/aImg/52547/c976641c-497d-4678-aa2f-ef972c4ff8ff-t.jpg" alt="A person sitting in a laboratory writing notes with a pen in a notebook." title="A person sitting in a laboratory writing notes with a pen in a notebook." loading="lazy"></picture></a></figure></section><sect